&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;There are three rules for writing the novel. Unfortunately, no one knows what they are.&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W._Somerset_Maugham"&gt;W. Somerset Maugham&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everyone has to &lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/write-in-your-own-voice/"&gt;develop their own writing style&lt;/a&gt;, based on their own strengths and weaknesses, on the subject matter, on the target audience, and sometimes on the target medium. As such, it is virtually impossible to prescribe rigid rules for writing that encompass all conceivable situations and styles.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>